        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 3:49AM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 349 AM MDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm over Mott, or 31 miles northeast of Hettinger, moving
north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mott.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
